quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  43,26,"And when Abraham said to his father and his people, 'Surely I am quit of that you serve"
  43,27,except Him who originated me; and He will guide me
  43,28,And he made it a word enduring among his posterity; haply so they would return
  43,29,"Nay, but I gave these and their fathers enjoyment of days, until the truth came unto them, and a manifest Messenger"
  43,30,"And when the truth came to them, they said, 'This is a sorcery, and in it we are unbelievers"
  43,31,"They say, 'Why was this Koran not sent down upon some man of moment in the two cities"
  43,32,"What, is it they who divide the mercy of the Lord? We have divided between them their livelihood in the present life, and raised some of them above others in rank, that some of them may take others in servitude; and the mercy of thy Lord is better than that they amass"
  43,33,"And were it not that mankind would be one nation, We would have appointed for those who disbelieve in the All-merciful roofs of silver to their houses, and stairs whereon to mount"
  43,34,"and doors to their houses, and couches whereon to recline"
  43,35,"and ornaments; surely all this is but the enjoyment of the present life, and the world to come with thy Lord is for the godfearing"